<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 19 at 5:07PM EST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Threat for Hazardous Travel this Evening in Far Northeast
Porter County...
Wind-whipped lake effect snow showers will develop this evening
and primarily affect far northeast Porter County and points east.
A light snow accumulation on untreated roadways will combine with
periods of low visibility to potentially cause hazardous travel
conditions, including along the Interstate 94 corridor. Check road
conditions at 5 1 1 in dot org before driving this evening. When
driving in snow, slow down and increase following distance.</description>
